Verant only says it's against the rules because it would ruin the integrity of the game if they said &quot;yes, you can buy and sell your gear on ebay, with our compliments&quot; because they know that people would make a full time job out of it. See, if you examine verants motives, it's not to keep the player happy, oh no. We're basically gerbils hitting a button to get food pellets, and they have given us a chat room to do it in as well. Nope, the player is happy to be simply 'playing' so they only thing Verant has to do is make sure that A) the player can see the rewards of continued playing and that B) they believe that the only way to get those rewards is to keep playing. <br>
